-- Russian Equity Movers: Aeroflot, Bank St Petersburg, Mechel
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-06-26T15:56:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/russian-equity-movers-aeroflot-mechel-severstal-shares-move.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 1
percent to 1,342.82 by the close in Moscow, gaining for the
first time in five days. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
advanced 2.1 percent to 1,288.67.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX) added 0.7 percent to 42.44 rubles,
the most since June 18. Shares rose for the first day in six on
bets the election of Russian opposition leader and anti-
corruption blogger Alexey Navalny to the state-controlled
airline’s board will improve efficiency.  Bank  St. Petersburg  (BSPB RX) lost 0.2 percent to 54.63
rubles, the lowest level since June 4. The shares dropped after
Citigroup Inc. cut its price estimate by 32 percent and removed
the regional lender from its top stock picks on disappointing
earnings.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)   gained 0.3 percent to 190.60 rubles,
the most since June 21. OAO Severstal (CHMF RX) rose 0.6 percent
to 377.80 rubles. Russia’s biggest producer of coking-coal for
steelmakers and the country’s second-largest steelmaker rose on
a forecast domestic product demand may jump 56 percent by 2020.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
